textBody:
Mercury usually refers to:

* Mercury (element), a metallic chemical element (symbol: Hg)
* Mercury (mythology), a Roman god
* Mercury (planet), first planet from the Sun

Mercury may also refer to:

Arts and entertainment

Fictional characters

* Mercury (Marvel Comics), a character who can turn herself into a mercurial substance
* Mercury (Amalgam Comics), a combination of the characters Impulse and Quicksilver
* Makkari (comics) or Mercury, an Eternal, a Marvel comics race of superhumans
* Mercury, a member of the Metal Men, a DC comics team
* Mercury, a member of Cerebro's X-Men
* Sailor Mercury, a character in the Sailor Moon franchise
* Mercury Black, a character in the RWBY web series

Literature

* Mercury (novel), 2005, by Ben Bova
* Mercury, a novel by Anna Kavan
* Mercury (magazine), an astronomy magazine
* Mercury (newspaper), any of several English-language newspapers

Music

Albums

* Mercury (Longview album)
* Mercury (American Music Club album)
* Mercury (Madder Mortem album)

Songs

* "Mercury" (song), 2008, by Bloc Party
* "Mercury", a song by Kathleen Edwards from Failer
* "Mercury", a song by Counting Crows from Recovering the Satellites
* "Mercury", a song by Sufjan Stevens, Bryce Dessner, Nico Muhly and James McAlister from Planetarium

Other uses in music

* Freddie Mercury (1946–1991), frontman for the rock group Queen
* Daniela Mercury (born 1965), Brazilian singer, songwriter and record producer
* Mercury Records, a record label
* Mercury Prize, an annual music prize awarded for the best album from the United Kingdom

Other media

* Mercury (TV series), from Australia
* Mercury FM, a radio station in Surrey, United Kingdom
* Mercury 96.6, present-day Heart Hertfordshire, a radio station in Hertfordshire, United Kingdom
* Archer Maclean's Mercury, a 2005 PlayStation Portable video game
* Bohemian Rhapsody (film), an upcoming film about Freddie Mercury that was originally announced with the title Mercury
* Mercury (2018 film)

Companies

* Mercury Communications, a British telecommunications firm set up in the 1980s
* Mercury Drug, a Philippine pharmacy chain
* Mercury Energy, an electricity generation and retail company in New Zealand
* Mercury Insurance Group
* The Mercury Mall, a shopping centre in Romford, England
* Mercury Marine, a major manufacturer of marine engines, particularly outboard motors
* Mercury Provident, a former British ethical bank
* Shuttle America, a regional airline (callsign "Mercury")

Military

* Operation Mercury, codename for the German invasion of Crete during World War II
* HMS Mercury, any of several ships of the Royal Navy
* USS Mercury, any of several ships of the United States Navy
* Boeing E-6 Mercury, an American aircraft used as an airborne command post and communications relay
* Miles Mercury, a British aircraft designed during the Second World War
* Russian brig Mercury, an 1820 warship

People

* Mercury (name), any of several people with that surname or given name
* Mercury Morris (born 1947), former American football player
* Freddie Mercury (1946–1991), frontman for the rock group Queen
* Daniela Mercury (born 1965), Brazilian singer, songwriter and record producer

Places

New Zealand

* Mercury Bay, on the North Island of New Zealand
* Mercury Islands, off the northeast coast of New Zealand

United States

* Mercury, Nevada, a closed city within the Nevada Test Site, United States
* Mercury Boulevard, a road in Virginia, United States

Elsewhere

* Mercury Fountain, in Tom Quad, Christ Church College, Oxford, England
* Mercury, Savoie, a commune in southeastern France

Science and technology

For vehicles, see .

Biology

* Mercurialis annua, a species of flowering plant known by the common name annual mercury
* Blitum bonus-henricus, a species of goosefoot known by the common names English mercury or mercury goosefoot, among other names

Computing

* Mercury Interactive, a software testing tools vendor
* Mercury (programming language)
* Mercury Systems, a defense-related information technology company
* Ferranti Mercury, an early 1950s commercial computer
** Mercury Autocode, a programming language for the Ferranti Mercury computer
* Mercury Mail Transport System, an email server

Other uses in science and technology

* Project Mercury, the first United States human spaceflight program
* Mercury (cipher machine)
* Mercury (plant), members of the plant genus Mercurialis
* Mercury (satellite)

Transportation

Land

* Mercury (automobile), produced by the Ford Motor Company from 1938 to 2011
* Mercury (cyclecar), an American cyclecar from 1914
* Mercury (train), a family of New York Central streamliner passenger trains (1936–1958)

Air

* Blackburn Mercury, a British aircraft from 1911
* Bristol Mercury, a nine-cylinder aircraft engine

Sports

* Edmonton Mercurys, a 1940s and 1950s intermediate ice hockey team from Canada
* Phoenix Mercury, a Women's National Basketball Association team from Arizona, United States
* Toledo Mercurys, a defunct International Hockey League franchise from Ohio, United States
* Fujita Soccer Club Mercury, a Japanese women's football team from 1989 to 1999

Other uses

* Mercury dime, a United States coin minted from 1916 through 1945
* "Mercury, the Winged Messenger", a movement in Gustav Holst's The Planets
